  "text": "There are many ways to reduce the elements of B to a stationary level, but what is sought is a way that is demographically plausible. In the single region model, a zero growth population projection matrix can be found by dividing every fertility rate by the population's Net Reproduction Rate (NRR). However, the NRR of a multiregional population is neither well defined nor easy to calculate. Simply dividing every element of B by λ B , the dominant eigenvalue of B, is not appropriate because that would reduce survivorship and migration as well as fertility. A reasonable way to achieve stationarity is to follow [CITATION_1] and assume that fertility rates decline so that the new rates are given by",
